location: 3882 Maizeland Rd Colorado Springs, CO 80909, Colorado Springs, Colorado
postcontent:
The Echo AR-II Trigger is a ground breaking drop in design that is approved by the ATF. 

The Echo AR-II Trigger allows the shooter to select from 3 different settings. 

Safe Mode: Firearm will not fire. 
Semi-Automatic Mode: Firearm fires when trigger is pulled. 
Echo Mode: Firearm fires when trigger is pulled and also when trigger is released. 

The Echo AR-II Trigger is designed with safety being the utmost priority. When the shooter is in the Echo Mode and depresses the trigger one round is fired, if the target moves, the shooter can move the selector to the safe position and a second round will not fire upon release. 
The ECHO AR-II TRIGGER has several distinct features: 
PATENTED Design that gained ATF Approval (Patent # US 8,820,211 B1)   
Technology licensed through HIPERFIRE inside the Echo Trigger 
Light, clean, and crisp pull in Semi-Automatic Mode 
The Echo AR-II Trigger is packed full of cutting edge technology 
Reliable function in Echo Mode .

MOS gives you the option of adding tall iron sights allowing the optic and the iron sights to co-witness. This pistol does not include the modular sight, just the bracket to mount it on. title: For Sale:  Complete H&K MR556A1 w/Optic
postcontent:
I have available for purchase a complete Heckler & Koch model MR556A1 rifle in .223/5.56mm with all items included from the factory.  The rifle was purchased new by a a collector of HK guns and is in excellent condition.  The MR556 is the civilian variant of the successful HK416 assault rifle.  The platform pairs the proven form factor of the AR-15 pattern rifle with a highly reliable short-stroke piston.  While this does add a small bit of weight the result is an even softer recoiling gun with extremely high build quality.  This particular weapon is of the earlier type with a full picatinny quad rail.Included:
-Factory Case
-Original Manual
-HK branded cable lock
-Original diaopter sights
-HK branded tool for adjustment and disassembly-The vertical grip is also an HK product and marked as such.  -TROY rail covers, the only non HK parts on the gun besides the optic.The weapon has less than 1000 rounds through its 16" barrel and the exterior is in very good condition with the painted factory markings still crisp and bright and the black finish unmarred.   This rifle is currently wearing an Eotech EXPS3 holographic weapon with a matching Eotech G33 magnifier on a flip to side mount.  This is an excellent pairing of optic and rifle, however should you not be interested the optic may be omitted and a comparable discount negotiated.
Please note that while all STANAG magazines will work perfectly well, first and second generation Magpul PMags will not lock into place properly with this rifle.  Current third generation PMags work without any problems.Contact me if you have any questions.  This is an excellent example of the type and it will be a great addition (or start!) to any HK collection.  Further pictures are available upon request!
As the rifle was purchased in California it does currently wear a 'bullet button' magazine lock, however the original magazine release will be included with your purchase and the weapon may be easily restored to standard condition once outside the state.  Due to the somewhat convoluted laws regarding firearm ownership in the state of California at this time, I am looking for buyers OUTSIDE of the state unless you are authorized to receive an assault weapon in California.  There is a small amount of exterior wear on the vertical grip from normal use.
